spec: mp3421
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 675 (mp3421): __hash__, __eq__, __lt__ dict-presence (hash(x), x==y, x<y) for multiprocessing types."
    - "Theme: __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ dict-presence (hash(x), x==y, x<y)."
    - "All values False — multiprocessing types are process-based concurrency primitives with no custom hash/eq/lt defined in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__hash__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __hash__. hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager with no __hash__ in its own __dict__ — process identity for hashing falls back to inherited object-level id-based hash. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types with no custom __hash__ in their own __dict__. managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __hash__ in its __dict__. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list does not define __hash__ (list is unhashable via __hash__ = None on the list type itself); BaseListProxy does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__ either. managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict similarly sets __hash__ = None; _BaseDictProxy does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__. managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set is unhashable; _BaseSetProxy does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__eq__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __eq__. == delegates to __eq__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types do not define __eq__ in their own __dict__; equality falls back to inherited identity comparison from object. The proxy types (_BaseSetProxy, _BaseDictProxy, BaseListProxy) relay operations to the managed server process, but do not define __eq__ in their own __dict__; equality testing falls back to inherited behavior. multiprocessing.Process: identity-based equality by inheritance; is_alive() provides liveness, not equality. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no __eq__ defined in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__lt__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __lt__. < delegates to __lt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__. The proxy types (_BaseSetProxy, _BaseDictProxy, BaseListProxy): while BaseListProxy defines __getitem__, __add__, __mul__ and other collection protocol methods in its __dict__, __lt__ is not among them. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types with no __lt__ in their own __dict__."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its types interact exclusively through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — not through comparison or hashing protocol overrides in any class __dict__."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 665 (mp3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 666 (mp3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 667 (mp3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 668 (mp3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 670 (mp3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 671 (mp3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 672 (mp3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 673 (mp3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 674 (mp3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 675 (mp3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __hash__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__hash__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __hash__.
# hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager; hashing falls
#   back to the inherited id-based hash from object. __hash__ is absent from
#   Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types
#   with no custom __hash__ defined in their own __dict__.
# managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __hash__ in its
#   __dict__.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list sets __hash__ = None on the
#   list type itself; BaseListProxy does not define __hash__ in its own
#   __dict__ (the list unhashability mechanism is on list, not BaseListProxy).
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict similarly sets __hash__ = None;
#   _BaseDictProxy does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set is unhashable; _BaseSetProxy
#   does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

